data.title: Sigma Phi Epsilon
data.text:
Sigma Phi Epsilon is redefining fraternity on college campuses across the country. We complement a manâ€™s education by delivering a premier student experience in one of the most formative times of his life. Through Sigma Phi Epsilon, men strengthen their character, build leadership and interpersonal skills, and learn to develop healthy, lifelong relationships that are essential to a successful and fulfilling life.

Nickname: SigEp

Colors: Purple, Red, and Gold

Flower: Violet and Dark Red Roses

Chapter: TN Eta

Founded Nationally: November 1, 1901 at Richmond College (now the University of Richmond)

Founded Locally: April 20, 1966

Philanthropy: Big Brothers Big Sisters of America (Nationally) and Cystic Fibrosis (Locally)

Sigma Phi Epsilon President: Nathan Maynard
